free.freechess
Class GameInfoStruct

java.lang.Object
  free.util.Struct
      free.freechess.GameInfoStruct

public class GameInfoStruct
extends Struct

A structure holding parsed information from a gameinfo line. See the "help iv_gameinfo" helpfile on freechess.org for information about the format.

GameInfoStruct

public GameInfoStruct(int gameNumber,
                      boolean isGamePrivate,
                      java.lang.String gameCategory,
                      boolean isGameRated,
                      boolean isWhiteRegistered,
                      boolean isBlackRegistered,
                      int whiteTime,

                      int partnerGameNumber,
                      int whiteRating,
                      char whiteProvShow,
                      int blackRating,
                      char blackProvShow,
                      boolean isWhiteTimesealed,
                      boolean isBlackTimesealed)
Creates a new GameInfoStruct with the specified arguments.

Parameters:
gameNumber - The game number.
isGamePrivate - Is the game private?
gameCategory - A string specifying the category of the game. This will contain the rating type if it's a chess game or the wild variant name if it's a wild game.
isGameRated - Is the game rated?
isWhiteRegistered - Is the white player registered?
isBlackRegistered - Is the black player registered?
whiteTime - The initial amount of time on white's clock, in seconds.
whiteInc - The amount of time white's clock is incremented by after each move he makes, in seconds.
blackTime - The initial amount of time on black's clock, in seconds.
blackInc - The amount of time black's clock is incremented by after each move he makes, in seconds.
partnerGameNumber - The game number of the bughouse partner, or 0 if it's not a bughouse game.
whiteRating - White's rating.
whiteProvShow - White's rating provshow character, 'E' is estimated, 'P' if provisional and ' ' if neither.
blackRating - Black's rating.
blackProvShow - Black's rating provshow character, 'E' is estimated, 'P' if provisional and ' ' if neither.
isWhiteTimesealed - Is the white player using timeseal.
isBlackTimesealed - Is the black player using timeseal.
Method Detail

parseGameInfoLine

public static GameInfoStruct parseGameInfoLine(java.lang.String line)
Parses a gameinfo line and returns a corresponding GameInfoStruct object. Sample line:
1 p=0 t=blitz r=1 u=1,1 it=5,5 i=8,8 pt=0 rt=1586E,2100 ts=1,0
